   - That is, `pc.fu_outer P p.outerParams = ⟪rotM (p.θ₂) (p.φ₂) P, pc.w⟫ / ‖P‖`.

2. Multiplying both sides by `‖P‖` gives exactly the desired inner product on the RHS:
   \[ \text{pc.fu\_outer P p.outerParams} \cdot \|P\| = ⟪rotM (p.θ₂) (p.φ₂) P, pc.w⟫. \]
   - And by definition, `p.outer P = rotM (p.θ₂) (p.φ₂) P`.
